    "details": {
      "blurb": "THE QUEEN — two souls, one crown (B20)",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "common",
          "infernal",
          "thassilonian",
          "varisian",
          "shadowtongue"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 21
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>THE FINAL BOSS (B20, the Everdawn Pool).</strong> Two souls wear one crown: the spoiled queen, and the seed of <strong>Kazavon</strong> ripening inside her. She floats in semi-trance at the Pool's heart (no need to breathe or eat) — <strong>10 days remain</strong> on the ritual (rule of thumb: the party gets two attempts; driven off twice, she finishes it — see What If Ileosa Wins). She notices entrants immediately unless they are very stealthy; sneaking to the Pool's center earns the PCs an automatic surprise round. <strong>She fights to the death at the Pool — no retreat, no parley, only fury.</strong> Only @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-items.Item.serithtialSword1]{Serithtial} truly ends her: suppress the regeneration, sunder the @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-items.Item.crownOfFangs0001]{Crown}, and the dragon-soul dies screaming. Killing her destabilizes the Pool: run <strong>the Rise of the Dragon</strong> immediately.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
